{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":280,"text":"One of the first patients\nI had to see as a pediatrician was Sol,"},{"time":5370,"text":"a beautiful month-old baby"},{"time":8150,"text":"who was admitted with signs\nof a severe respiratory infection."},{"time":11830,"text":"Until then, I had never seen\na patient worsen so fast."},{"time":16810,"text":"In just two days\nshe was connected to a respirator"},{"time":19810,"text":"and on the third day she died."},{"time":22550,"text":"Sol had whooping cough."},{"time":25300,"text":"After discussing the case in the room\nand after a quite distressing catharsis,"},{"time":30460,"text":"I remember my chief resident said to me,"},{"time":32509,"text":"\"Okay, take a deep breath. Wash your face."},{"time":36430,"text":"And now comes the hardest part:"},{"time":39050,"text":"We have to go talk to her parents.\""},{"time":42150,"text":"At that time, a thousand questions\ncame to mind,"},{"time":46120,"text":"from, \"How could a one-month-old\nbaby be so unfortunate?\""},{"time":51200,"text":"to, \"Could we have done\nsomething about it?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":55400,"text":"Before vaccines existed,"},{"time":57680,"text":"many infectious diseases\nkilled millions of people per year."},{"time":63100,"text":"During the 1918 flu pandemic"},{"time":66630,"text":"50 million people died."},{"time":69780,"text":"That's greater than Argentina's\ncurrent population."},{"time":73060,"text":"Perhaps, the older ones among you\nremember the polio epidemic"},{"time":77110,"text":"that occurred in Argentina in 1956."},{"time":80240,"text":"At that time, there was no vaccine\navailable against polio."},{"time":83560,"text":"People didn't know what to do.\nThey were going crazy."},{"time":86090,"text":"They would go painting trees\nwith caustic lime."},{"time":88370,"text":"They'd put little bags of camphor"},{"time":89940,"text":"in their children's underwear,\nas if that could do something."},{"time":94080,"text":"During the polio epidemic,\nthousands of people died."},{"time":98600,"text":"And thousands of people were left\nwith very significant neurological damage."},{"time":104650,"text":"I know this because I read about it,"},{"time":107290,"text":"because thanks to vaccines,\nmy generation was lucky"},{"time":111080,"text":"to not live through an epidemic\nas terrible as this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113890,"text":"Vaccines are one of the great successes\nof the 20th century's public health."},{"time":119210,"text":"After potable water,"},{"time":121230,"text":"they are the interventions\nthat have most reduced mortality,"},{"time":124840,"text":"even more than antibiotics."},{"time":127570,"text":"Vaccines eradicated terrible diseases\nsuch as smallpox from the planet"},{"time":132590,"text":"and succeeded in significantly\nreducing mortality"},{"time":136200,"text":"due to other diseases such as measles,"},{"time":138450,"text":"whooping cough, polio and many more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142320,"text":"All these diseases are considered\nvaccine-preventable diseases."},{"time":149910,"text":"What does this mean?"},{"time":151670,"text":"That they are potentially preventable,"},{"time":154690,"text":"but in order to be so,\nsomething must be done."},{"time":157660,"text":"You need to get vaccinated."},{"time":160270,"text":"I imagine that most,\nif not all of us here today,"},{"time":163970,"text":"received a vaccine\nat some point in our life."},{"time":168510,"text":"Now, I'm not so sure that many of us know"},{"time":172960,"text":"which vaccines or boosters\nwe should receive after adolescence."},{"time":178710,"text":"Have you ever wondered\nwho we are protecting"},{"time":182790,"text":"when we vaccinate?"},{"time":185070,"text":"What do I mean by that?"},{"time":186700,"text":"Is there any other effect\nbeyond protecting ourselves?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":193050,"text":"Let me show you something."},{"time":195760,"text":"Imagine for a moment"},{"time":198220,"text":"that we are in a city"},{"time":200230,"text":"that has never had a case\nof a particular disease,"},{"time":203480,"text":"such as the measles."},{"time":205430,"text":"This would mean that no one in the city\nhas ever had contact with the disease."},{"time":210290,"text":"No one has natural defenses against,\nnor been vaccinated against measles."},{"time":215680,"text":"If one day, a person sick with the measles\nappears in this city"},{"time":221000,"text":"the disease won't find much resistance"},{"time":224510,"text":"and will begin spreading\nfrom person to person,"},{"time":227440,"text":"and in no time it will disseminate\nthroughout the community."},{"time":231810,"text":"After a certain time"},{"time":233530,"text":"a big part of the population will be ill."},{"time":237750,"text":"This happened when there were no vaccines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242630,"text":"Now, imagine the complete opposite case."},{"time":247420,"text":"We are in a city"},{"time":249830,"text":"where more than 90 percent\nof the population"},{"time":252650,"text":"has defenses against\nthe measles, which means"},{"time":255100,"text":"that they either had the disease,\nsurvived, and developed natural defenses;"},{"time":258839,"text":"or that they had been\nimmunized against measles."},{"time":263200,"text":"If one day,"},{"time":264810,"text":"a person sick with the measles\nappears in this city,"},{"time":269230,"text":"the disease will find much more resistance"},{"time":272610,"text":"and won't be transmitted\nthat much from person to person."},{"time":276780,"text":"The spread will probably remain contained"},{"time":280750,"text":"and a measles outbreak won't happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285060,"text":"I would like you\nto pay attention to something."},{"time":288810,"text":"People who are vaccinated"},{"time":291490,"text":"are not only protecting themselves,"},{"time":294290,"text":"but by blocking the dissemination\nof the disease"},{"time":297900,"text":"within the community,"},{"time":299540,"text":"they are indirectly protecting\nthe people in this community"},{"time":304220,"text":"who are not vaccinated."},{"time":306690,"text":"They create a kind of protective shield"},{"time":309660,"text":"which prevents them from\ncoming in contact with the disease,"},{"time":312760,"text":"so that these people are protected."},{"time":316670,"text":"This indirect protection"},{"time":319870,"text":"that the unvaccinated people\nwithin a community receive"},{"time":323370,"text":"simply by being surrounded\nby vaccinated people,"},{"time":327950,"text":"is called herd immunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333130,"text":"Many people in the community"},{"time":335590,"text":"depend almost exclusively\non this herd immunity"},{"time":339090,"text":"to be protected against disease."},{"time":342760,"text":"The unvaccinated people you see\nin infographics are not just hypothetical."},{"time":347260,"text":"Those people are our nieces\nand nephews, our children,"},{"time":350600,"text":"who may be too young\nto receive their first shots."},{"time":355100,"text":"They are our parents, our siblings,"},{"time":357410,"text":"our acquaintances,"},{"time":358840,"text":"who may have a disease,"},{"time":360710,"text":"or take medication\nthat lowers their defenses."},{"time":366010,"text":"There are also people who are\nallergic to a particular vaccine."},{"time":371350,"text":"They could even be among us,"},{"time":373750,"text":"any of us who got vaccinated,"},{"time":375610,"text":"but the vaccine didn't produce\nthe expected effect,"},{"time":379410,"text":"because not all vaccines\nare always 100 percent effective."},{"time":383600,"text":"All these people depend\nalmost exclusively on herd immunity"},{"time":388800,"text":"to be protected against diseases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392390,"text":"To achieve this effect of herd immunity,"},{"time":397200,"text":"it is necessary that a large percentage\nof the population be vaccinated."},{"time":402500,"text":"This percentage is called the threshold."},{"time":405570,"text":"The threshold depends on many variables:"},{"time":409330,"text":"It depends on the germ's characteristics,"},{"time":411740,"text":"and those of the immune response\nthat the vaccine generates."},{"time":416040,"text":"But they all have something in common."},{"time":418430,"text":"If the percentage of the population\nin a vaccinated community"},{"time":423980,"text":"is below this threshold number,"},{"time":427050,"text":"the disease will begin\nto spread more freely"},{"time":431110,"text":"and may generate an outbreak\nof this disease within the community."},{"time":435780,"text":"Even diseases which were \nat some point controlled may reappear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444550,"text":"This is not just a theory."},{"time":446740,"text":"This has happened,\nand is still happening."},{"time":451050,"text":"In 1998, a British researcher\npublished an article"},{"time":455750,"text":"in one of the most important\nmedical journals,"},{"time":458530,"text":"saying that the MMR vaccine,"},{"time":461150,"text":"which is given for measles,\nmumps and rubella,"},{"time":463880,"text":"was associated with autism."},{"time":465750,"text":"This generated an immediate impact."},{"time":469010,"text":"People began to stop getting vaccinated,\nand stopped vaccinating their children."},{"time":473680,"text":"And what happened?"},{"time":475300,"text":"The number of people vaccinated,"},{"time":477980,"text":"in many communities around the world,\nfell below this threshold."},{"time":481960,"text":"And there were outbreaks of measles\nin many cities in the world --"},{"time":485520,"text":"in the U.S., in Europe."},{"time":487960,"text":"Many people got sick."},{"time":490120,"text":"People died of measles."},{"time":493870,"text":"What happened?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":495350,"text":"This article also generated a huge stir\nwithin the medical community."},{"time":500020,"text":"Dozens of researchers began to assess\nif this was actually true."},{"time":505130,"text":"Not only could no one find"},{"time":508420,"text":"a causal association between MMR\nand autism at the population level,"},{"time":513669,"text":"but it was also found that this article\nhad incorrect claims."},{"time":518820,"text":"Even more, it was fraudulent."},{"time":522120,"text":"It was fraudulent."},{"time":525120,"text":"In fact, the journal publicly retracted\nthe article in 2010."},{"time":532880,"text":"One of the main concerns and excuses\nfor not getting vaccinated"},{"time":536780,"text":"are the adverse effects."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539770,"text":"Vaccines, like other drugs,\ncan have potential adverse effects."},{"time":545970,"text":"Most are mild and temporary."},{"time":548480,"text":"But the benefits are always greater\nthan possible complications."},{"time":555740,"text":"When we are ill,\nwe want to heal fast."},{"time":560300,"text":"Many of us who are here"},{"time":562420,"text":"take antibiotics\nwhen we have an infection,"},{"time":566090,"text":"we take anti-hypertensives\nwhen we have high blood pressure,"},{"time":569270,"text":"we take cardiac medications."},{"time":571450,"text":"Why? Because we are sick\nand we want to heal fast."},{"time":574700,"text":"And we don't question it much."},{"time":576720,"text":"Why is it so difficult\nto think of preventing diseases,"},{"time":581890,"text":"by taking care of ourselves\nwhen we are healthy?"},{"time":585100,"text":"We take care of ourselves a lot\nwhen affected by an illness,"},{"time":588290,"text":"or in situations of imminent danger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592140,"text":"I imagine most of us here,"},{"time":594810,"text":"remember the influenza-A pandemic"},{"time":598540,"text":"which broke out in 2009\nin Argentina and worldwide."},{"time":602490,"text":"When the first cases\nbegan to come to light,"},{"time":605520,"text":"we, here in Argentina,\nwere entering the winter season."},{"time":609910,"text":"We knew absolutely nothing."},{"time":612120,"text":"Everything was a mess."},{"time":613530,"text":"People wore masks on the street,\nran into pharmacies to buy alcohol gel."},{"time":618900,"text":"People would line up\nin pharmacies to get a vaccine,"},{"time":622250,"text":"without even knowing\nif it was the right vaccine"},{"time":624810,"text":"that would protect them\nagainst this new virus."},{"time":627350,"text":"We knew absolutely nothing."},{"time":629650,"text":"At that time, in addition to doing\nmy fellowship at the Infant Foundation,"},{"time":634740,"text":"I worked as a home pediatrician\nfor a prepaid medicine company."},{"time":639670,"text":"I remember that I started\nmy shift at 8 a.m.,"},{"time":642910,"text":"and by 8, I already had a list\nof 50 scheduled visits."},{"time":647060,"text":"It was chaos;\npeople didn't know what to do."},{"time":650860,"text":"I remember the types of patients\nthat I was examining."},{"time":655690,"text":"The patients were a little older than\nwhat we were used to seeing in winter,"},{"time":660050,"text":"with longer fevers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662390,"text":"And I mentioned that\nto my fellowship mentor,"},{"time":666070,"text":"and he, for his part, had heard\nthe same from a colleague,"},{"time":669590,"text":"about the large number\nof pregnant women"},{"time":672320,"text":"and young adults"},{"time":674010,"text":"being hospitalized in intensive care,"},{"time":676250,"text":"with hard-to-manage clinical profiles."},{"time":680760,"text":"At that time, we set out to understand\nwhat was happening."},{"time":687300,"text":"First thing Monday morning,\nwe took the car"},{"time":690420,"text":"and went to a hospital\nin Buenos Aires Province,"},{"time":693350,"text":"that served as a referral hospital\nfor cases of the new influenza virus."},{"time":699020,"text":"We arrived at the hospital;\nit was crowded."},{"time":701550,"text":"All health staff were dressed\nin NASA-like bio-safety suits."},{"time":705470,"text":"We all had face masks in our pockets."},{"time":707670,"text":"I, being a hypochondriac,\ndidn't breathe for two hours."},{"time":710400,"text":"But we could see what was happening."},{"time":713520,"text":"Immediately, we started\nreaching out to pediatricians"},{"time":717210,"text":"from six hospitals in the city\nand in Buenos Aires Province."},{"time":721440,"text":"Our main goal was to find out"},{"time":724770,"text":"how this new virus behaved\nin contact with our children,"},{"time":728660,"text":"in the shortest time possible."},{"time":731240,"text":"A marathon work."},{"time":734200,"text":"In less than three months,"},{"time":737070,"text":"we could see what effect\nthis new H1N1 virus had"},{"time":743160,"text":"on the 251 children\nhospitalized by this virus."},{"time":749520,"text":"We could see which children\ngot more seriously ill:"},{"time":753500,"text":"children under four, especially those\nless than one year old;"},{"time":757120,"text":"patients with neurological diseases;"},{"time":759920,"text":"and young children\nwith chronic pulmonary diseases."},{"time":763210,"text":"Identifying these at-risk groups\nwas important"},{"time":768020,"text":"to include them as priority groups"},{"time":770730,"text":"in the recommendations\nfor getting the influenza vaccine,"},{"time":773730,"text":"not only here in Argentina,"},{"time":775590,"text":"but also in other countries\nwhich the pandemic not yet reached."}]},{"cues":[{"time":780750,"text":"A year later,"},{"time":782430,"text":"when a vaccine against the pandemic\nH1N1 virus became available,"},{"time":787520,"text":"we wanted to see what happened."},{"time":790240,"text":"After a huge vaccination campaign"},{"time":793410,"text":"aimed at protecting at-risk groups,"},{"time":798180,"text":"these hospitals, with 93 percent\nof the at-risk groups vaccinated,"},{"time":805140,"text":"had not hospitalized a single patient"},{"time":808770,"text":"for the pandemic H1N1 virus."},{"time":811450,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":815920,"text":"In 2009: 251."},{"time":821490,"text":"In 2010: zero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824440,"text":"Vaccination is an act\nof individual responsibility,"},{"time":829220,"text":"but it has a huge collective impact."},{"time":834790,"text":"If I get vaccinated,\nnot only am I protecting myself,"},{"time":839420,"text":"but I am also protecting others."},{"time":843520,"text":"Sol had whooping cough."},{"time":847500,"text":"Sol was very young,"},{"time":849700,"text":"and she hadn't yet received\nher first vaccine against whooping cough."},{"time":855160,"text":"I still wonder what would have happened"},{"time":858960,"text":"if everyone around Sol\nhad been vaccinated."},{"time":865740,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}